Description: Fragment of conical foot of large East Greek(?) pottery cup; outside glazed; underside reserved; 'symbol' cut on inner surface of foot.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Buried in sand under the west wall of Temenos.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 672)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.231)
